Global leaders, including U.S. President Biden, European Commission President von der Leyen, and UK Prime Minister Johnson, discussed the importance of infrastructure initiatives that promote economic growth and combat the climate crisis. They emphasized the need for infrastructure to be climate resilient and developed through a climate lens. Strong partnerships between host countries, developed countries, and the private sector were also highlighted as crucial for sustainable infrastructure development. The leaders endorsed the principles of financing, constructing, and maintaining infrastructure in accordance with high standards, including environmental, social, and governance standards. They emphasized the need for a new paradigm of climate finance, involving both public and private sources, to mobilize the trillions of dollars needed to achieve net-zero emissions by 2050. Additionally, they emphasized the role of climate-smart infrastructure development in boosting economic recovery and creating sustainable jobs. The leaders called on countries worldwide to make similar commitments and take action to promote reliable, climate-smart infrastructure.